Discharge Instructions for Tunneled Pleural Catheter (PleurX)

Daily Drainage Instructions:
- Wash hands thoroughly before handling the catheter.
- Gather supplies: drainage kit, alcohol pads, gloves.
- Clean the valve cap with alcohol pad for 15 seconds.
- Connect the drainage line to the catheter valve and open the clamp to allow drainage.
- Monitor drainage amount and color; stop drainage when flow stops or if experiencing chest pain or shortness of breath.
- Close clamp and disconnect drainage line; clean and replace valve cap securely.
- Record amount and color of fluid drained.

When to Call:
